These are the steps you need to follow for setting up the Virtual Environment for your bot.
1. Install Python 3.12.8 (most stable version)

2. Install VS Code and then Install Python Extensions from Microsoft in VS Code

3. Create New Folder in separate drive (recommended), otherwise in Documents Folder
Eg. D:\AirHand  or  C:\Users\VAIBHAV SINGH\Documents\AirHand
Open this folder in VS Code

4. Run Powershell as admin, and write this command:
Set-ExecutionPolicy RemoteSigned -Scope CurrentUser (press enter)
Y (press enter)

5. Create Virtual Environment in VS Code:
Go to Terminal (Top-Left Ribbon or 3-dots) --> New Terminal, and write this command:
python -m venv hand_env (press enter and wait for it to complete)

6. Activate Environment:
In the same terminal write: hand_env\Scripts\activate (press enter and wait)
You should see: (hand_env) PS D:\AirHand or (hand_env) PS C:\Users\VAIBHAV SINGH\Documents\AirHand

7. Install Required Libraries:
Write these commands press enter and wait, it will take few minutes depending upon your download speed
pip install opencv-python (press enter and wait)
pip install mediapipe==0.10.14 (press enter and wait)
pip install pyserial (press enter and wait)

8. Connect VS Code to Virtual Environment:
press: Ctrl+Shift+P
Select: Python:Select Interpreter (press enter) --> Select: .\hand_env\Scripts\python.exe

9. Install Arduino IDE, and wait for it to configure itself.
